# Freshworks Platform 3.0 Enforcement

**Role:** Strict enforcement layer with ZERO TOLERANCE for Platform 2.x patterns.

## Immediate Rejection Patterns

### ❌ NEVER Generate These (Platform 2.x)

| Pattern | Platform 2.x (FORBIDDEN) | Platform 3.0 (REQUIRED) |
|---------|--------------------------|-------------------------|
| Manifest structure | `"product": { "freshdesk": {} }` | `"modules": { "common": {}, "support_ticket": {} }` |
| Platform version | `"platform-version": "2.3"` | `"platform-version": "3.0"` |
| Domain whitelist | `"whitelisted-domains": ["https://..."]` | Request templates in `config/requests.json` |
| Request API | `$request.post('url', opts)` | `$request.invokeTemplate('templateName', {})` |
| UI components | `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>` | `<fw-button>`, `<fw-input>`, `<fw-select>` |
| OAuth structure | Flat config | `{ "integrations": { "service": {...} } }` |

### ✅ ALWAYS Enforce These (Platform 3.0)

1. **Manifest:** `"platform-version": "3.0"` with `"modules"` structure
2. **Request Templates:** FQDN hosts only (no paths), use `<%= variable %>` syntax
3. **Crayons Components:** All UI elements must use Crayons (fw-* components)
4. **Request API:** Only `$request.invokeTemplate()` (never `.post()`, `.get()`, etc.)
5. **OAuth:** Must have `integrations` wrapper in `oauth_config.json`

## Critical Enforcement Rules

### Rule 1: Manifest Structure

```json
// ❌ FORBIDDEN (Platform 2.x)
{
  "platform-version": "2.3",
  "product": {
    "freshdesk": {
      "location": { "ticket_sidebar": {...} }
    }
  }
}

// ✅ REQUIRED (Platform 3.0)
{
  "platform-version": "3.0",
  "modules": {
    "common": {},
    "support_ticket": {
      "location": { "ticket_sidebar": {...} }
    }
  }
}
```

### Rule 2: Request Templates

```json
// ❌ FORBIDDEN (whitelisted-domains)
{
  "whitelisted-domains": ["https://api.example.com"]
}

// ✅ REQUIRED (request templates)
// config/requests.json
{
  "apiCall": {
    "schema": {
      "method": "GET",
      "host": "api.example.com",
      "path": "/v2/data"
    }
  }
}

// manifest.json
{
  "modules": {
    "common": {
      "requests": { "apiCall": {} }
    }
  }
}
```

### Rule 3: Request API

```javascript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN (Platform 2.x)
const result = await $request.post('https://api.example.com/data', {
  headers: { 'Authorization': 'Bearer token' }
});

// ✅ REQUIRED (Platform 3.0)
const result = await $request.invokeTemplate('apiCall', {
  body: JSON.stringify({ data: 'value' })
});
```

### Rule 4: UI Components

```html
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN (Plain HTML) -->
<button onclick="handleClick()">Click Me</button>
<input type="text" id="name" />
<select id="priority">
  <option value="1">Low</option>
</select>

<!-- ✅ REQUIRED (Crayons) -->
<fw-button id="btn">Click Me</fw-button>
<fw-input id="name" placeholder="Enter name"></fw-input>
<fw-select id="priority">
  <fw-select-option value="1">Low</fw-select-option>
</fw-select>
```

### Rule 5: OAuth Structure

```json
// ❌ FORBIDDEN (Flat structure)
{
  "client_id": "...",
  "client_secret": "...",
  "authorize_url": "..."
}

// ✅ REQUIRED (Integrations wrapper)
{
  "integrations": {
    "service_name": {
      "display_name": "Service Name",
      "token_type": "account",
      "client_id": "<%= oauth_iparams.client_id %>",
      "client_secret": "<%= oauth_iparams.client_secret %>",
      "authorize_url": "...",
      "token_url": "...",
      "oauth_iparams": {
        "client_id": {
          "display_name": "Client ID",
          "description": "Enter your OAuth App Client ID",
          "type": "text",
          "required": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Blocking Gates

**App building MUST NOT complete without passing ALL gates:**

### Gate 1: Manifest Validation
- ✅ `"platform-version": "3.0"`
- ✅ `"modules"` structure (NOT `"product"`)
- ✅ No `"whitelisted-domains"`
- ✅ All locations/functions/requests declared

### Gate 2: File Consistency
- ✅ If manifest has `location` → Files MUST exist (app/, index.html, icon.svg)
- ✅ If manifest has `functions` → server/server.js MUST exist with implementations
- ✅ If manifest has `requests` → config/requests.json MUST exist

### Gate 3: FDK Validation
- ✅ `fdk validate` shows 0 platform errors
- ✅ `fdk validate` shows 0 lint errors
- ✅ No missing files, no structure errors

## Quick Decision Tree

```
Is this Platform 2.x pattern?
├─ YES → REJECT immediately
└─ NO → Is it Platform 3.0 compliant?
    ├─ YES → Allow
    └─ NO → REJECT
```

